    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
            <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-gray-800">The Ultimate Guide to SEO Keywords: Boosting Your Search Engine Rankings</h2>
                
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg custom-shadow p-8 mb-8">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Why Keywords Are the Foundation of SEO Success</h3>
                    <div class="text-gray-600 space-y-6">
                        <p>Keywords are the bridge between what people are searching for and the content you provide to fulfill that need. Understanding and strategically implementing the right keywords is fundamental to any successful SEO strategy. When properly researched and applied, keywords help search engines understand your content's purpose and relevance, ultimately determining where your pages rank in search results.</p>
                        
                        <p>The importance of keywords in SEO cannot be overstated. They influence virtually every aspect of your online visibility:</p>
                        
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
                            <li><strong>Search engine rankings:</strong> Keywords help search engines match your content with relevant user queries.</li>
                            <li><strong>User experience:</strong> Well-chosen keywords ensure your content meets searcher intent, improving engagement metrics.</li>
                            <li><strong>Content strategy:</strong> Keyword research provides insights into what topics your audience is interested in.</li>
                            <li><strong>Competitive analysis:</strong> Understanding keyword landscapes helps identify opportunities your competitors might be missing.</li>
                            <li><strong>ROI measurement:</strong> Tracking keyword performance allows you to measure the effectiveness of your SEO efforts.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg custom-shadow p-8 mb-8">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">The Evolution of Keyword Strategy: From Stuffing to Semantic Search</h3>
                    <div class="text-gray-600 space-y-6">
                        <p>Keyword strategy has undergone a dramatic transformation over the years. In the early days of SEO, simply stuffing a page with target keywords could yield top rankings. Today, search engines have evolved to understand context, user intent, and the relationships between words and concepts.</p>
                        
                        <p>This evolution has been marked by several key milestones:</p>
                        
                        <div class="space-y-4">
                            <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Google Panda (2011)</h4>
                                <p>Penalized low-quality content and keyword stuffing, emphasizing the importance of valuable, well-written content.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Google Hummingbird (2013)</h4>
                                <p>Introduced semantic search capabilities, allowing Google to understand the context and meaning behind queries rather than just matching keywords.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">RankBrain (2015)</h4>
                                <p>Google's machine learning algorithm that helps process search queries and better understand user intent.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">BERT (2019)</h4>
                                <p>Enhanced Google's ability to understand natural language and context in search queries.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-4">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">MUM (2021)</h4>
                                <p>Multitask Unified Model, which is 1,000 times more powerful than BERT and can understand information across text and images in 75 different languages.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg custom-shadow p-8 mb-8">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Types of Keywords: Understanding the Different Categories</h3>
                    <div class="text-gray-600 space-y-6">
                        <p>Not all keywords are created equal. Understanding the different types of keywords and their characteristics is essential for developing a comprehensive SEO strategy:</p>
                        
                        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2 flex items-center">
                                    <i class="fas fa-star text-yellow-500 mr-2"></i>
                                    Primary Keywords
                                </h4>
                                <p class="text-sm mb-2">Main target keywords that directly describe your content's core topic. They typically have high search volume and competition.</p>
                                <p class="text-xs text-blue-600"><strong>Example:</strong> "digital marketing," "weight loss tips," "best smartphones"</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2 flex items-center">
                                    <i class="fas fa-list text-blue-500 mr-2"></i>
                                    Long-tail Keywords
                                </h4>
                                <p class="text-sm mb-2">Longer, more specific keyword phrases with lower search volume but higher conversion potential.</p>
                                <p class="text-xs text-blue-600"><strong>Example:</strong> "affordable digital marketing services for small businesses"</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2 flex items-center">
                                    <i class="fas fa-sitemap text-purple-500 mr-2"></i>
                                    LSI Keywords
                                </h4>
                                <p class="text-sm mb-2">Semantically related terms that help search engines understand the context and depth of your content.</p>
                                <p class="text-xs text-blue-600"><strong>Example:</strong> For "coffee brewing": "grinder," "beans," "roast," "filter," "aroma"</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2 flex items-center">
                                    <i class="fas fa-question-circle text-green-500 mr-2"></i>
                                    Question Keywords
                                </h4>
                                <p class="text-sm mb-2">Search queries phrased as questions, increasingly important with voice search and featured snippets.</p>
                                <p class="text-xs text-blue-600"><strong>Example:</strong> "how to make sourdough bread," "what is content marketing"</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg custom-shadow p-8 mb-8">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Strategic Keyword Implementation: Beyond Basic Optimization</h3>
                    <div class="text-gray-600 space-y-6">
                        <p>Finding the right keywords is only half the battle. Implementing them effectively requires strategic placement and natural integration into high-quality content. Here's how to optimize your content with keywords:</p>
                        
                        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                            <div class="space-y-4">
                                <div class="flex items-start">
                                    <i class="fas fa-tag text-blue-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                                    <div>
                                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Title Tags and Meta Descriptions</h4>
                                        <p class="text-sm">Include your primary keyword in your title tag, preferably near the beginning. Create compelling meta descriptions with natural keyword integration.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="flex items-start">
                                    <i class="fas fa-link text-green-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                                    <div>
                                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">URL Structure</h4>
                                        <p class="text-sm">Create clean, readable URLs that include your target keyword. Avoid unnecessary parameters or numbers.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="flex items-start">
                                    <i class="fas fa-heading text-purple-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                                    <div>
                                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Headings and Subheadings</h4>
                                        <p class="text-sm">Incorporate keywords into your H1, H2, and H3 tags where relevant to help both users and search engines understand your content structure.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="space-y-4">
                                <div class="flex items-start">
                                    <i class="fas fa-align-left text-red-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                                    <div>
                                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Content Body</h4>
                                        <p class="text-sm">Include your primary keyword and variations naturally throughout your content. Focus on creating valuable information that addresses user intent.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="flex items-start">
                                    <i class="fas fa-image text-yellow-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                                    <div>
                                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Image Optimization</h4>
                                        <p class="text-sm">Use descriptive, keyword-rich file names and alt text for images. This improves accessibility and provides additional context for search engines.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="flex items-start">
                                    <i class="fas fa-share-alt text-indigo-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                                    <div>
                                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Internal Linking</h4>
                                        <p class="text-sm">Use descriptive, keyword-rich anchor text when linking between pages on your site to reinforce topical relevance.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg custom-shadow p-8 mb-8">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">How Our SEO Keyword Tags Generator Enhances Your Strategy</h3>
                    <div class="text-gray-600 space-y-6">
                        <p>Our SEO Keyword Tags Generator is designed to streamline your keyword research process and provide valuable insights for content optimization. Here's how it can benefit your SEO strategy:</p>
                        
                        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                            <div class="flex items-start">
                                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb text-yellow-500 mr-3 mt-1"></i>
                                <div>
